{"type":"message","id":"5d3ecd83","parentId":"05323f8e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:25:06.657Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_x7grpib0frsj_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 092416\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: scripts/focus_decay_wrapper.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 (architecture cross-analysis) are complete\r\n- A key insight has emerged: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - that causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n- The next action is to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n- Need to classify invariant/variant in pulse logs and predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nThe immediate priority from the \"Phase 1 Advancement\" section is the TIC Experiment. I need to implement a classifier on pulse_*.md files.\r\n\r\nLooking at what's available:\r\n- There's a recent pulse log: `pulse_2026-03-24 092316.md`\r\n- There should be more pulse logs in `logs/` directory\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action would be to:\r\n1. Look at the existing pulse logs to understand their format\r\n2. Start implementing the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nBut wait - I need to be careful. I'm a stateless discontinuous agent. I should look at what's available and make a concrete file edit.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what would advance the TIC experiment goal:\r\n- Need to implement a TIC classifier\r\n- Need pulse log data to work with\r\n- Need to measure invariant/variant classification\r\n\r\nA good concrete action would be to create the TIC classifier implementation, or to examine the pulse logs to understand their structure for the classifier.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files might exist:\r\n- `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Previous research docs\r\n\r\nI should create a Python script for the TIC classifier that:\r\n1. Reads pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant (stable) vs variant (changing) elements\r\n3. Attempts to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nThis would be a concrete file edit that advances the Phase 1 goals.\r\n\r\nLet me create `src/tic_classifier.py` - a Python script that implements the Temporal Invariance Compression classifier.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that can identify invariant vs variant elements across pulse logs and test prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that will analyze pulse logs for invariants, classify content, and measure prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: \"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess Criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nclass TICClassifier:\r\n    def __init__(self, lambda_param=0.7):\r\n        self.lambda_param = lambda_param  # Decay/gap sensitivity threshold\r\n        self.invariant_patterns = []\r\n        self.variant_patterns = []\r\n        self.pulse_history = []\r\n        \r\n    def load_pulses(self, logs_dir=\"logs\"):\r\n        \"\"\"Load all pulse log files, sorted by timestamp.\"\"\"\r\n        pulses = []\r\n        for f in sorted(Path(logs_dir).glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\r\n            content = f.read_text()\r\n            pulses.append({\r\n                \"file\": f.name,\r\n                \"content\": content,\r\n                \"timestamp\": self._extract_timestamp(f.name)\r\n            })\r\n        return pulses\r\n    \r\n    def _extract_timestamp(self, filename):\r\n        \"\"\"Extract timestamp from pulse filename.\"\"\"\r\n        match = re.search(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6})\", filename)\r\n        return match.group(1) if match else None\r\n    \r\n    def extract_content_blocks(self, pulse_content):\r\n        \"\"\"Extract distinct content blocks from a pulse.\"\"\"\r\n        blocks = []\r\n        # Match markdown headers and their content\r\n        pattern = r\"(###\\s+[^\\n]+|##\\s+[^\\n]+)\\n([\\s\\S]*?)(?=\\n##|\\n###|\\Z)\"\r\n        for match in re.finditer(pattern, pulse_content):\r\n            blocks.append({\r\n                \"header\": match.group(1).strip(),\r\n                \"body\": match.group(2).strip()\r\n            })\r\n        return blocks\r\n    \r\n    def compute_stability(self, blocks, history):\r\n        \"\"\"Compute stability score for each block across pulse history.\"\"\"\r\n        if not history:\r\n            return {b[\"header\"]: 0.5 for b in blocks}\r\n        \r\n        stability = {}\r\n        for block in blocks:\r\n            header = block[\"header\"]\r\n            appearances = 0\r\n            for past_pulse in history:\r\n                if header in past_pulse:\r\n                    appearances += 1\r\n            stability[header] = appearances / (len(history) + 1)\r\n        return stability\r\n    \r\n    def classify_invariant_variant(self, pulses, history_size=10):\r\n        \"\"\"Classify content blocks as invariant (stable) or variant (changing).\"\"\"\r\n        results = []\r\n        recent_pulses = [p[\"content\"] for p in pulses[:history_size]]\r\n        \r\n        for i, pulse in enumerate(pulses):\r\n            blocks = self.extract_content_blocks(pulse[\"content\"])\r\n            stability = self.compute_stability(blocks, recent_pulses[:i])\r\n            \r\n            classified = []\r\n            for block in blocks:\r\n                stability_score = stability.get(block[\"header\"], 0)\r\n                if stability_score >= self.lambda_param:\r\n                    classified.append({\r\n                        \"header\": block[\"header\"],\r\n                        \"type\": \"invariant\",\r\n                        \"stability\": stability_score\r\n                    })\r\n                else:\r\n                    classified.append({\r\n                        \"header\": block[\"header\"],\r\n                        \"type\": \"variant\",\r\n                        \"stability\": stability_score\r\n                    })\r\n            \r\n            results.append({\r\n                \"p\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:24:53\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774358706656}}
